Task 1-
User & Group + Permissions
•	Create a user john with a home directory /home/team/john.
•	Create a group teamlead and make john a member.
•	Create a directory /project/data owned by john:teamlead.
•	Set permissions so only owner and group can access it.
(Others should have no permission.)

solution:-

1st create user by using command
- useradd -m -d /home/team/john john
  * m for home directory /home/john
  * d for home directory change /home/team/john
2nd create group by using groupadd command
- groupadd teamlead
3rd create directory
- mkdir -p /project/data
4th owner is john and group is teamlead
- chown john:teamlead /project/data
5th change permissions owner and group can access other is denied
- chmod 770 /project/data
To verify 
- ls -ld /project/data
drwxrwx---. 2 john teamlead 6 Nov 15 21:46 /project/data/

